      <body>I don't think that it is a bug. I think there is a reason why you can't use dots.

If you are interested here is a regexp for such route:

@@@
/\A\/issues\/([^\/.?]+)(?:\.([^\/.?]+))?\Z/
@@@

Here are segments (for better understanding) for this route:

@@@
segments: [&quot;/issues/&quot;, /(?&lt;id&gt;\A[^/.?]+\Z)/, [&quot;.&quot;, /(?&lt;format&gt;\A[^/.?]+\Z)/]]
@@@

I think you can't use dots because of format segment but i'm not sure, any ideas why dot is not allowed?</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;I don't think that it is a bug. I think there is a reason why
you can't use dots.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested here is a regexp for such route:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code&gt;/\A\/issues\/([^\/.?]+)(?:\.([^\/.?]+))?\Z/&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here are segments (for better understanding) for this route:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code&gt;segments: [&quot;/issues/&quot;, /(?&amp;lt;id&amp;gt;\A[^/.?]+\Z)/, [&quot;.&quot;, /(?&amp;lt;format&amp;gt;\A[^/.?]+\Z)/]]&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I think you can't use dots because of format segment but i'm not
sure, any ideas why dot is not allowed?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
